        "-children":[
          {
            "#comment":"To make the lamp go on and off, a TouchSensor is routed into a 'toggle' script that alternates between TRUE and FALSE outputs, sending TRUE on the first TRUE input, then FALSE on the next TRUE input. These TRUE/FALSE values are routed into a SpotLight node within the lamp, turning it on and off."
          },
          {
            "#comment":"A second script converts an incoming TRUE or FALSE in to one of two colors. Those colors are routed into the lamp's bulb to change it from an on color to an off color."
          },
          {
            "#comment":"Note that .x3d XML syntax uses boolean constants true/false instead of VRML syntax TRUE/FALSE"
